@echo off rem Echo illustrating how to get batch file folder and its parent folder.
rem Determine the folder that this batch file exists in: rem - used to provide path relative to the batch file location set scriptFolder=%~dp0 rem Remove trailing \ from scriptFolder set scriptFolder=%scriptFolder:~0,-1% rem Also get the script name without leading path. set scriptName=%~nx0
rem Get the parent folder, which is the folder for the full software install. rem Have to get parent folder using Windows for loop approach. for %%i in (%scriptFolder%) do set installFolder=%%~dpi rem Remove trailing \ from installFolder set installFolder=%installFolder:~0,-1%
echo scriptFolder=%scriptFolder% echo installFolder=%installFolder%
exit /b 0
